    <h1>Test Writing Process</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div style=3D"display: none;">
<br>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"TestWritingProcess-1a.TransferManualTestCase">1a. Transfer Manual=
 Test Case</h1>
<ul>
<li>Copy test steps as placeholder keywords</li>
<li>Expected results should be 'Log' lines</li>
<li>Expect that the manual test steps will not look exactly like the automa=
ted test steps</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"TestWritingProcess-1b.OrCreateNewAutomatedTestCase">1b. Or Create=
 New Automated Test Case</h1>
<ul>
<li>Create a Test Name describing an action and expected result</li>
<li>To help develop the test using the Given-When-Then Gherkin syntax can h=
elp identify smaller steps</li>
<li>It is always desirable to have only one assertion per test</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"TestWritingProcess-2.IdentifyKeywords">2. Identify Keywords</h1>
<ul>
<li>Evaluate Keyword coverage of test</li>
<li>Can test be executed with existing keywords?</li>
<li>Are new keywords needed?</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"TestWritingProcess-3.CreateNewKeywordsOrUseExistingKeywords">3. C=
reate New Keywords Or Use Existing Keywords</h1>
<ul>
<li>If New Keywords are needed, then page objects and interfaces will need =
to be developed</li>
<li>If Existing Keywords can be used then are there any special modificatio=
ns needed?</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"TestWritingProcess-4.DevelopKeywordsFromTestToResourceToLibrary">=
4. Develop Keywords From Test To Resource To Library</h1>
<ul>
<li>Keywords should move from the test downward.</li>
<li>Keyword abstraction should be limited to two levels. (for the sake of t=
he robot report)</li>
<li>Page Object Model design is preferred, moving to an interface layer.</l=
i>
<li>Cascading resource design is preferred (higher level resources pull fro=
m lower level resources)</li>
<li>If a resource is either too complex to understand or is going to be use=
d in multiple projects- move the resource to a python library</li>
<li>If a keyword is only being used for a particular test, it should stay w=
ith the test (you can always move it)</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"TestWritingProcess-5.ImplementBestTestSuiteApproach">5. Implement=
 Best Test Suite Approach</h1>
<ul>
<li>Is this going to be a set of single tests?</li>
<li>Is this going to be a templated test?</li>
<li>How are the test setups and teardowns going to be managed?</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"TestWritingProcess-6.CleanTheTestCode">6. Clean The Test Code</h1=
>
<ul>
<li>Use Robotidy first and always when cleaning up test code</li>
<li>Use --dryrun flag to troubleshoot basic RF issues (importing libraries,=
 variables, etc ...)</li>
<li>Use Robocop last or close to the end</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"TestWritingProcess-7.SubmitForCodeReview">7. Submit For Code Revi=
ew</h1>
